fields.value: Synoptic maps for Lagrangian L1 and L5 modeling

dsDescriptionValue.value: Two sets of Near-Real-Time (NRT) synoptic maps from SOLIS/VSM. One is a complete (used for modeling "true" distribution of magnetic field on the Sun, and another with two isolated bipolar active regions removed to model the observations from L1 point.

publicationCitation.value: Weinzierl, M., Mackay, D. H., Yeates, A. R., Pevtsov, A. A., 2016, "The Possible Impact of L5 Magnetograms on Non-Potential Solar Coronal Magnetic Field Simulations", Astrophis. J., 828, 102
Pevtsov, A.A., Bertello, L. , MacNeice, P., and Petrie, G.: 2016, "What if we had a magnetograph at Lagrangian L5?", Space Weather, 14

fields.value: Compressed fits files containing NRT synoptic maps from SOLIS/VSM (solis.nso.edu). Files marked with "L1" represent L1 viewing point. Those without this letter mark represent data with combined L1+L5 maps.
